-- Egypt Will Remove Industry Subsidies Over Time, Ahram Reports
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-10-09T06:58:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-09/egypt-will-remove-industry-subsidies-over-time-ahram-reports.html
Egypt  plans gradually to remove
subsidies for the cement, fertilizer and iron and steel
industries, the state-run Ahram reported, citing Hatem Saleh,
the industry and foreign trade minister.  The policy, which was agreed on during a national dialogue
between the government and businessmen, will also include the
gradual removal of subsidies for the food industry, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
